Crown and root lengths were measured and analyzed by using a method developed by Lind [27] and modified by Holtta et al. [28]. Midpoint was visually determined along a line bisecting the buccal and lingual cemento-enamel junctions (CEJ) (Fig. 2). All the teeth measured were single-rooted teeth as only anterior teeth were included. Thus, each root was measured from the apex to the corresponding midpoint. All crown heights were measured from the CEJ midpoints perpendicular to the incisal/occlusal reference line (formed tangent to incisal edge or buccal cusps). Root resorption for an individual tooth was assessed using the following formula:
